720305f-a.title: Manhattan: Hamilton Place - 138th Street (West)
720305f-a.text:
Hamilton Place, at the N.E. corner of West 138th Street.
About 1922.
Gift of E. M. Jenks.
MAY BE REPRODUCED.

715614f-a.title: Manhattan: 138th Street (West) - Hamilton Place
715614f-a.text:
West 138th Street, east from Hamilton Place, to and including Amsterdam
Ave., showing on the right a portion of the Hebrew Orphan Asylum. The
low structure atop the hill (S.E. corner of Amsterdam Ave.) is the entrance
to the Lewisohn Stadium.
June 5, 1936.
W.P.A. Photo.
Federal Art Project.
CREDIT LINE IMPERATIVE ON ALL REPRODUCTIONS.
